The paper deals with the problem of allocating objects to rational agents, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The allocation problem is specified in terms of a weighted graph, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of graph theory (cs.DS). The paper proposes a solution concept of stability, which is a common concept in mechanism design and social choice theory (cs.AI). The paper also discusses computational complexity results for computing stable allocations, which suggests that the paper may be relevant to the field of computational complexity (cs.LG). Finally, the paper studies the notion of envy-freeness, which is a common fairness criterion in allocation problems (cs.SI).
